    "industrial_process_notes": "Melamine or urea is condensed with formaldehyde (idealized MF product: hexa-hydroxymethyl melamine) to form a crosslinked thermoset. Formaldehyde is more tightly bound in MF than in UF, giving MF resins lower formaldehyde emissions. UF was first synthesized (unrecognized as a polymer) by Hölzer and Bernhard Tollens in 1884; Hanns John obtained the first Austrian patent for UF resin in 1919; Carl Goldschmidt patented UF as a disinfectant in 1897. ~20 million tonnes of UF produced annually, >70% for wood-composite bonding.",
